WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.000
We engineered Shakti Seva Studio to answer a narrow civic technology question.

00:00:05.000 --> 00:00:11.000
Can a community advocate use local AI to explain public housing repair records without losing the evidence?

00:00:11.000 --> 00:00:13.000
A polished answer was not enough.

00:00:13.000 --> 00:00:18.000
We wanted a person to run one case on a laptop and inspect every step.

00:00:18.000 --> 00:00:21.000
The current prototype starts with a New York City building address.

00:00:21.000 --> 00:00:24.000
It keeps complaints and violations separate.

00:00:24.000 --> 00:00:27.000
It removes apartment information before a building search.

00:00:27.000 --> 00:00:31.000
It shows where each fact came from and which action the code selected.

00:00:31.000 --> 00:00:38.000
This talk explains the application layer, the AI layer, the proof, and what remains unknown.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:42.000
The application is a local Python service with three interfaces.

00:00:42.000 --> 00:00:48.000
A command line tool, a browser, and the Hermes terminal interface all use the same case record.

00:00:48.000 --> 00:00:52.000
FastAPI serves the browser on the loopback address.

00:00:52.000 --> 00:00:58.000
A same-origin WebSocket carries typed progress, case, trace, and error messages.

00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:00.000
The case service…
